&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Content Development Manager&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: Remote&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;(CA, AZ, TX, FL and NY)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Springboard&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Springboard combines world-class online learning with high-touch human support — including dedicated mentors, career coaches, and student advisors — to help people change or advance their careers. From our AI and tech upskilling programs to our growing suite of Allied Health certification programs, we build learning experiences that help people change their lives.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for a seasoned &lt;strong&gt;Content Development Manager &lt;/strong&gt;to join our Learning Experience (LX) team. In this role, you&#39;ll own the end-to-end creation of high-quality instructional content across our programs — ranging from AI and tech courses to healthcare certification programs — helping adult learners successfully change or uplevel their careers.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our ideal candidate is comfortable operating at both 30,000 feet and 3 feet: someone who can flex between being in the details while building towards the bigger picture. You might be asked to conceptualize and build a new course end-to-end to drive ambitious learner outcomes, build relationships and work with SME/instructors to shape their presentational content week-over-week, or dive into the details to do a careful proofreading pass of written content. Our ideal candidate possesses a “learning producer” mindset: you understand how content presented live should support and connect to content consumed asynchronously, and the strengths of different formats and modalities.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for someone who brings an eye to detail, obsession with high-quality content and learning experiences, and creative range to everything they build.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the full lifecycle of course content development across multiple modalities. We’re looking for someone who has a wide range of content development experience across written learning materials, instructional video, live sessions (eg., webinars), audio content, and beyond.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a “Learning Producer” for new courses – developing a vision for both synchronous and asynchronous learning components of courses – and executing on that vision.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write, edit, and proofread instructional content to a high standard of clarity, accuracy, and learner-friendliness, leveraging AI tools.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build relationships and collaborate closely with subject matter experts, instructors, and presenters to refine, elevate and gamify lectures and presentations.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage AI tools to accelerate and enhance content development workflows.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner cross-functionally with project managers, the LX team, client-facing teams, and other internal stakeholders to ensure content meets business objectives and launch timelines.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and continuously improve content quality standards across the team.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8–10 years of experience in learning design, content development, and/or course development.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated end-to-end ownership of course creation — from concept through final production.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Content development experience across modalities: written content, video production, live/webinar facilitation, learning games, audio/podcast production, etc.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional writing, proofreading, and editing skills. You

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Influencer Partnerships Specialist (Contract)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Remote&amp;nbsp; |&amp;nbsp; Part-Time Contract (20 hrs/week)&amp;nbsp; |&amp;nbsp; U.S., Canada, Mexico &amp;amp; Latin America&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Springboard&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Springboard is an online education company that helps people make career-defining moves through mentor-led, outcome-driven programs. Our portfolio includes Tech Bootcamps (Software Engineering, Data Science, UI/UX, Cybersecurity) and Allied Health training (Certified Medical Assistant, Pharmacy Technician, Sterile Technician) — all focused on helping working professionals and career switchers land high-growth roles.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Influencer partnerships are a meaningful and growing channel for Springboard. We have existing creator relationships, working infrastructure, and real enrollment data. What we need is someone who can take what’s here and make it work harder — better creators, better outreach, better deal economics, more enrollments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a part-time contract role (20 hours/week) focused on the part of influencer marketing that matters most: &lt;strong&gt;finding the right creators and getting them to say yes on terms that work.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll inherit an existing influencer program with active partnerships, tracked performance history, and established tools. Your job is not to rebuild it from scratch — it’s to improve it. Better sourcing. Sharper evaluation. Smarter outreach. Tighter deal structures. More signed creators who actually drive enrollments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll work across two product lines with very different audiences and economics — Tech Bootcamps and Allied Health. The right person can navigate both — understanding that the creators, messaging, and deal structures for a $14K bootcamp are fundamentally different from a $4,500 healthcare credential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Most of your time (~70%) goes to creator discovery and outreach:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Find creators whose audiences match Springboard’s buyers. &lt;/strong&gt;Source across YouTube, Instagram, and TikTok in niches like tech careers, career switching, coding tutorials, productivity, healthcare careers, and professional development. Prioritize U.S.-audience-dominant creators.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Evaluate creators with a practitioner’s eye. &lt;/strong&gt;Go beyond follower counts. Read engagement quality, audience demographics, sponsored content history, view-to-subscriber ratios, and comment sentiment. Know when a creator’s metrics look good on paper but won’t convert for a high-ticket education product.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Run outreach that gets responses. &lt;/strong&gt;Write personalized outreach at volume without sacrificing quality. Manage follow-up cadences. Build relationships with creators and their managers. You should be comfortable running outreach as a core daily activity, not as an afterthought.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Negotiate deals that protect our economics. &lt;/strong&gt;Structure compensation (flat fee, affiliate, hybrid) that aligns creator incentives with enrollment outcomes. Push back on rates that don’t pencil. You’ll have target CPAs to work within, and we expect you to treat them seriously.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The remaining ~30% supports campaign setup and performance:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Set up tracking infrastructure for each partnership. &lt;/strong&gt;Create UTM links, coupon codes, and influencer-specific landing pages so every partnership is measurable from day one.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Coordinate content and approvals. &lt;/strong&gt;Work with crea

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Type&lt;/strong&gt;: Part-time (Up to 20 hours per week); Contract&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location&lt;/strong&gt;: Remote&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Duration&lt;/strong&gt;: Project-based (with potential to extend)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Springboard&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Springboard is an online learning platform focused on helping learners build real-world skills and launch or advance their careers. Core to our success is our human-guided support model featuring mentors, instructors, career coaches, and advisors to help students succeed. Through this hybrid approach, we’ve helped thousands of learners revamp their careers and, by extension, their lives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We partner closely with industry experts to design cutting-edge, outcomes-driven programs. We’re currently building a new &lt;strong&gt;Agentic AI course&lt;/strong&gt; and are looking for a Learning Producer/Course General Manager to help shape, design, and launch the first iteration of this program.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re seeking a &lt;strong&gt;Learning Producer / Course General Manager&lt;/strong&gt; to lead the development and initial delivery of a new, 7-8 week Agentic AI course for Fortune 1000 professionals. This role sits at the intersection of learning design, content production, and program execution, in close collaboration with SMEs and guest lecturers. You’ll work closely with Springboard leadership and Agentic AI subject matter experts to ensure the course is not only effective and comprehensive, but the best in its category. Our primary goals are delivering a fantastic learner experience and producing exceptional outcomes.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a hands-on, highly collaborative role ideal for someone who has entrepreneurial experience and/or who is unquestionably a builder. We’re looking for someone who excels at both strategic thinking and execution in fast-moving, ambiguous environments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Course Research &amp;amp; Strategy&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct an analysis of 5-6 existing, reputable Agentic AI courses and programs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate topic areas covered, capstone projects / labs featured, and strengths of different courses and instructors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop a point of view on what a cutting-edge Agentic AI course &lt;em&gt;must&lt;/em&gt; include for today’s learners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help identify and select course talent (instructors) for the program&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Course Design&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define the high-level course structure and outline, use of instructor talent, learning objectives, and capstone project / assessment approach, consulting with Springboard’s CEO and Director of Learning Experience Design as thought partners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Agentic AI SMEs and instructors to shape the curriculum&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Content Development &amp;amp; Production&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with 5–8 lecturers (Agentic AI SMEs) to develop lecture-based content&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Edit and finalize lecture presentation content and PPT design, to align with overall course outline and flow&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create original, text-based materials and other supplementary content as needed, as wrap-around content to live lectures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure content is coherent, high-quality, and aligned with the overall learning experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Program Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee instructor contracting/negotiating, scheduling, and coordination&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage timelines and deliv

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Overview:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Springboard recently launched a 16-week online course for aspiring clinical medical assistants to learn the didactic and task knowledge needed to pass NHA’s CCMA exam, and matriculate into an Externship and full-time Medical Assistant roles. Springboard is looking to hire a Live Course Instructor to supplement the self-directed components of the program.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facilitate two live sessions weekly every week for 15 weeks (13 weeks of didactic content, plus 2 weeks of exam review). Sessions will be 1 hour each.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare independently for live sessions (up to 4 additional hours per week).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and modify lecture decks as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;On Weeks 1-13, your live sessions will review key concepts covered in the curriculum, and create space for student Q &amp;amp; A. You may also be asked to support with course announcements and other course housekeeping at the beginning/end of sessions.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gamify learning by introducing tools like Kahoot into live sessions.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;On the 2 exam study weeks, additional office hours may be requested.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Respond to student messages through our Course Advisors (by email) that require medical assisting&amp;nbsp; expertise, within a given SLA.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor Canvas discussion boards for weekly student responses and questions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assignment grading per week may also be required.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Armed with an understanding of best practices and various approaches to delivering &lt;strong&gt;CCMA&lt;/strong&gt;-aligned education online, apply your subject matter expertise in:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Critical clinical skill development, to train certified clinical MAs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Medical Terminology and Anatomy &amp;amp; Physiology&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Healthcare Administration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clinical Communication best practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Appropriate depth of content for entry-level MA training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;MA scope of practice&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;How to recreate skill-based training outside of a lab or clinical environment, while students learn at home.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An understanding of need-to-know versus nice-to-know didactic knowledge and task knowledge for CCMAs in training.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You may be called upon to:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with Springboard&#39;s Learning Experience team and Instructional Designers to adjust session content as needed.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Other needs as they arise&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working as a CCMA or CMA in a clinical setting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience training Clinical Medical Assisting online. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5-10 years of total professional experience, at minimum.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience using online teaching tools (eg: Canvas, Zoom).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong presentation and facilitation skills among large audiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong student empathy and excellent communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You live and work in the US.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pay: Up to $40 an hour pending location and experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Remote work for aspiring part-time medical assistants or premed students.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you an aspiring healthcare professional looking to make an impact while you study? &lt;strong&gt;Springboard&lt;/strong&gt; is seeking a motivated, research-oriented intern to help us build the ultimate resource hub for allied health students.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you will bridge the gap between clinical knowledge and digital storytelling. You will dive deep into the requirements of the healthcare industry and create the &quot;blueprint&quot; for success for future Medical Assistants, Phlebotomists, and CNAs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your work will directly influence the career paths of thousands of students. You will be responsible for:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Research:&lt;/strong&gt; Investigating certification pathways, state-by-state regulations, and the evolving challenges of the medical assistant profession.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Expert Content Creation:&lt;/strong&gt; Drafting authoritative articles, &quot;Day in the Life&quot; guides, and career roadmaps for aspiring allied health workers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Multimedia Storytelling:&lt;/strong&gt; Scripting and recording short-form video content that highlights the daily realities, skills, and rewards of working in a clinical setting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Resource Development:&lt;/strong&gt; Identifying &quot;pain points&quot; for students and developing checklists or study guides to help them succeed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We’re Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Career Alignment:&lt;/strong&gt; You are currently a pre-med student or aspiring toward a career as a Certified Medical Assistant (CMA), CNA, Nurse, or Technician.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strong Communicator:&lt;/strong&gt; You can translate complex medical or regulatory information into engaging, fluent English for a wide audience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Digital Native:&lt;/strong&gt; Comfortable recording video content and using digital research tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Detail-Oriented:&lt;/strong&gt; You have a &quot;clinical&quot; eye for detail and can ensure all research is accurate and up-to-date.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High School Diploma or GED.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be 18 years of age or older.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Legally authorized to work in the United States.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to pass a mandatory background check.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Springboard&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Springboard is a leading provider of Allied Health training, recognized for our hands-on externships and personalized student support. Our &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.springboard.com/courses/medical-assistant-career-track/&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Certified Medical Assistant Program&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is a leader in the field, dedicated to placing students in high-demand roles and helping them launch lifelong careers in healthcare.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This remote flexible role can be based in any of these states: CA, FL, TX, MA, AZ, NY &amp;amp; IL&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Company&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Springboard is a fast-growing education and workforce development company on a mission to bridge critical skills gaps by enabling individuals to access high-quality, job-aligned training. We partner directly with employers, healthcare systems, and workforce organizations to design and deliver programs that build durable talent pipelines in allied health, technology, and other high-demand fields, producing measurable business and workforce outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Opportunity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Senior Manager, B2B Marketing will play a central role in supporting Springboard’s B2B sales and partnership efforts across healthcare and enterprise workforce segments. This role is ideal for a self-directed, action-oriented marketer who can move fluidly from strategy to hands-on execution and thrives in ambiguous, fast-moving environments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be responsible for helping Springboard show up credibly and compellingly in front of senior buyers through in-person events, content, and sales enablement—translating customer needs into clear positioning, messaging, and marketing assets that drive pipeline and revenue impact.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&#39;ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pipeline &amp;amp; Revenue Growth:&lt;/strong&gt; Own and execute Springboard’s B2B marketing strategy to drive high-quality leads and accelerate partnership growth within the healthcare and enterprise sectors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Event Management:&lt;/strong&gt; Lead Springboard’s presence at priority industry events—from identifying high-impact sponsorships to managing booth execution and designing &quot;post-event&quot; nurture tracks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sales Enablement &amp;amp; Asset Creation:&lt;/strong&gt; Develop a high-performance library of sales tools, including pitch decks, one-pagers, ROI calculators, and tailored proposals that help win complex, multi-stakeholder deals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Account-Based Marketing (ABM):&lt;/strong&gt; Partner with Sales/BD to launch targeted campaigns for &quot;must-win&quot; accounts, using personalized content and multi-channel touches to break into senior-level committees.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Authority &amp;amp; Content Engine:&lt;/strong&gt; Produce credible, data-driven content (white papers, thought leadership pieces, case studies) that positions Springboard as a premier solution for workforce development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product Marketing &amp;amp; Positioning:&lt;/strong&gt; Bridge the gap between Product and Sales by translating technical program features into clear, outcome-oriented value propositions for enterprise buyers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Measurement &amp;amp; Optimization:&lt;/strong&gt; Establish a feedback loop with sales to track lead quality and asset performance, rapidly iterating on messaging based on real-world market response.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
